place.name: SPIXWORTH
place.gazetteerText: SPIXWORTH, a parish in St. Faith district, Norfolk; 5 miles N by E of Norwich r. station. Post town, Norwich. Acres, 1,224. Real property, £2,227. Pop., 44. Houses, 8. The manor, with S. Hall, belongs to J. Longe, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £362.* Patron, J. Longe, Esq. The church is good. Archbishop Hoadley was rector. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
